customer_type: however, I’ve tried to do my appointment at Gharda online and haven’t been possible. I visited the office, but they say appointments should be on online only. On the web I can’t select a date, is this because there is no availability and i should keep trying ? Or I am doing something wrong ?

I asked the foreign office in Germany, and they told me that I probably don’t need a visa for Ireland, and they are sure that I can extend my Blue Card there and come back to Germany using the same card. When I checked on the internet, I found Ireland to be not part of the “blue card” agreement, and when I told the foreign office, they said Ireland has a similar type to the blue card (i.e., exchangeable).
